    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for Ghost Ride the WHIP centers around the elite upside of **Corbin Carroll** (75.04) and **Josh Naylor** (72.22), our two highest-projected starters. **Corbin Carroll** remains the engine of this offense, benefiting from an advantageous #3 spot and a favorable matchup against Sproat (4.17 xERA). Meanwhile, **Josh Naylor** is in a prime position to capitalize on a +11% SP skill adjustment against Bradley; his presence in the cleanup slot is projected to yield significant RBI opportunities. While we remain thin on stolen base specialists in today\u2019s specific matchup set, the efficiency of **James Wood** (62.73) at the top of the order provides the necessary catalyst to set the table for our middle-order power hitters.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the card was keeping **Austin Riley** (43.75) on the bench. Despite his pedigree, the matchup against Skubal (2.71 xERA) suppressed his ceiling below our 40.0-floor threshold for starting eligibility. Conversely, **Kyle Karros** (60.75) and **Trevor Story** (59.77) were elevated due to soft matchups. **Trevor Story** is a particularly intriguing play; though his base projection is modest, his elite BvP history against Lauer provides the necessary bump to start him over high-ceiling options facing tougher arms. We are keeping a close watch on **Mickey Moniak**, whose score of 53.64 is heavily buoyed by Williamson\u2019s 6.11 xERA, though his platoon disadvantage acts as a significant drag on his overall efficiency.\n\nRisk mitigation remains the priority for Ghost Ride the WHIP. We have benched **Jose Caballero** (39.32) as he fell just shy of our scoring floor, primarily due to Eovaldi\u2019s dominant SP profile. We remain heavily invested in **Dalton Rushing** (56.26) and **Brice Turang** (62.62) to provide the daily consistency required to maintain our AVG standing, but owners should be wary of weather volatility in any game where a pitcher like Eovaldi or Skubal is throwing. As of this report, **Vinnie Pasquantino** remains sidelined, and we continue to monitor the status of **Giancarlo Stanton**, **Seiya Suzuki**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Max Muncy**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Carson Williams**, and **Tyler Soderstrom** for potential late-week rotations. For now, we trust the high-floor profile of **Luis Campusano** (46.24) to hold the catcher spot steady while our core assets work against these identified pitching vulnerabilities.",
